From: knsol <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH] fix: add FS_O_CREATE to write_to_file so a01.txt is created on first write

After 90 s of fresh-boot idle (no BLE), file_num_array stays [0, 0],
which means get_file_size("/SD:/audio/a01.txt") returns 0 — i.e. the
file either doesn't exist or fs_stat fails. cmd24 writes do happen on
the SPI bus (we saw 1 in 8 s), but they can't be writes to a01.txt if
the file isn't there.

Two omi bugs combine to leave a01.txt missing after mount:

  1. initialize_audio_file (sdcard.c:228) has a use-after-free:

         char *header = generate_new_audio_header(num);
         if (header == NULL) return -1;
         k_free(header);          /* freed here */
         create_file(header);     /* read here -> UB */
         return 0;

     The freed memory may still contain "audio/a01.txt" or may already
     hold the next allocator's payload. On this build/board the file
     ends up not getting created.

  2. write_to_file (sdcard.c:215) opens with FS_O_WRITE | FS_O_APPEND
     but no FS_O_CREATE. Zephyr/FATFS does NOT create the file on this
     flag combination — fs_open returns -ENOENT silently. Since
     write_to_file ignores all return codes, every subsequent
     fs_write/fs_close is a no-op on an uninitialized fs_file_t.

Minimal fix: add FS_O_CREATE to write_to_file. The first time it
runs, a01.txt is created if missing; thereafter APPEND extends it.
This is safer than fixing initialize_audio_file's use-after-free —
write_to_file is the actual hot path and we want it self-healing.
---
diff --git a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
--- a/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
+++ b/omi/firmware/devkit/src/sdcard.c
@@ -215,7 +215,11 @@ int write_to_file(uint8_t *data, uint32_t length)
 int write_to_file(uint8_t *data, uint32_t length)
 {
     struct fs_file_t write_file;
     fs_file_t_init(&write_file);
     uint8_t *write_ptr = data;
-    fs_open(&write_file, write_buffer, FS_O_WRITE | FS_O_APPEND);
+    /* Patch 0034: add FS_O_CREATE so the file is created on first
+     * write. omi's initialize_audio_file has a use-after-free that
+     * leaves a01.txt missing after mount on this board, and FS_O_APPEND
+     * alone does not create. */
+    fs_open(&write_file, write_buffer, FS_O_WRITE | FS_O_APPEND | FS_O_CREATE);
     fs_write(&write_file, write_ptr, length);
     fs_sync(&write_file);
     fs_close(&write_file);
